HEVC
High Efficiency Video Coding (HEVC) is a video compression standard, a successor to H.264/MPEG-4 AVC (Advanced Video Coding).HEVC is said to double the data compression ratio compared to H.264/MPEG-4 AVC at the same level of video quality. It can alternatively be used to provide substantially improved video quality at the same bit rate.

How to play HEVC
If you want to play this smoothly, you need to use a device/PC with at least dual-core processor.You have to update your player to latest version.
